{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891779335,"sessionID":"ses_2849c7c13ffe8wC3uB19j2tPvE","part":{"id":"prt_d7b660e5f001uVEjVpVTFHD0UF","messageID":"msg_d7b64a3c0001VqICBwBZUVclOF","sessionID":"ses_2849c7c13ffe8wC3uB19j2tPvE","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-2c7d6c75757846008ac7dd0be264a4d0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# pkg/workloadmanager ‚Äî Go Unit Testing Design\n\n## AR-038 ‚Äî Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: L\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the comprehensive unit testing strategy for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module, which provides HTTP API services for creating and managing agent runtime sandboxes, session lifecycle management, and integration with Kubernetes API and Redis storage.\n\n## Testing Architecture\n\n### Test Organization\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ api/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ types.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ response.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ response_test.go         # HTTP response utilities tests\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ (api_handlers_test.go)   # Future: API handler tests\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ controller/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sandbox.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sandbox_test.go          # Sandbox controller tests\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ (reconciler_test.go)     # Future: Reconciler tests\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler_test.go          # HTTP handler tests\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sandbox.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ sandbox_test.go          # Sandbox-specific handler tests\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ client/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ k8s_client.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ k8s_client_test.go       # Kubernetes client tests\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ config_test.go           # Configuration tests\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ middleware/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ middleware.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ middleware_test.go       # HTTP middleware tests\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ gc/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ collector.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ collector_test.go        # GC collector tests\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ policy.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ policy_test.go           # GC policy tests\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ scheduler.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ scheduler_test.go        # GC scheduler tests\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ metrics.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ metrics_test.go          # GC metrics tests\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ types/\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ sandbox_types.go\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ garbage_collector.go\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ garbage_collector_test.go    # Legacy garbage collector tests\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ defaults.go\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ design.md                    # This document\n```\n\n### Testing Strategy\n\n#### Unit Test Levels\n\n1. **Component-Level Tests**: Test individual functions and methods in isolation\n2. **Integration-Level Tests**: Test interactions between closely related components\n3. **Behavioral Tests**: Test end-to-end behavior using mocked dependencies\n\n#### Test Categories\n\n1. **Happy Path Tests**: Verify correct behavior with valid inputs\n2. **Error Path Tests**: Verify error handling and edge cases\n3. **Boundary Condition Tests**: Test limits and thresholds\n4. **Concurrency Tests**: Verify thread-safety where applicable\n5. **Performance Tests**: Verify performance characteristics (optional)\n\n### Testing Framework\n\n#### Standard Library + Third-Party Libraries\n\n```go\n// Testing framework\nimport \"testing\"\n\n// Assertion library\nimport \"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\nimport \"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\nimport \"github.com/stretchr/testify/mock\"\n\n// HTTP testing\nimport \"net/http/httptest\"\n\n// Kubernetes fake clients\nimport \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\nimport \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n\n// Redis testing\nimport \"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2\"\n```\n\n#### Test Helpers\n\nCommon test utilities to be created:\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/testing/fakes.go\npackage testing\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"testing\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2\"\n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/mock\"\n    corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n    wmClient \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/client\"\n)\n\n// TestFixtures provides common test data and helpers\ntype TestFixtures struct {\n    T           *testing.T\n    MiniRedis   *miniredis.Miniredis\n    Store       store.Store\n    FakeDynamic dynamic.Interface\n    FakeK8s     kubernetes.Interface\n    MockStore   *MockStore\n    MockK8s     *MockK8sClient\n}\n\n// NewTestFixtures creates a new test fixtures setup\nfunc NewTestFixtures(t *testing.T) *TestFixtures {\n    mr := miniredis.RunT(t)\n    redisStore, err := store.NewValkeyStore(mr.Addr(), \"\", 0)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    v1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n\n    return &TestFixtures{\n        T:           t,\n        MiniRedis:   mr,\n        Store:       redisStore,\n        FakeDynamic: fake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme),\n        FakeK8s:     fake.NewSimpleClientset(),\n        MockStore:   NewMockStore(),\n        MockK8s:     NewMockK8sClient(),\n    }\n}\n\n// Cleanup performs cleanup operations\nfunc (tf *TestFixtures) Cleanup() {\n    tf.Store.Close()\n    tf.MiniRedis.Close()\n}\n\n// Helper functions for creating test objects\nfunc CreateTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace string) *unstructured.Unstructured {\n    return &unstructured.Unstructured{\n        Object: map[string]interface{}{\n            \"apiVersion\": \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\",\n            \"kind\":       \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n                \"name\":      name,\n                \"namespace\": namespace,\n            },\n            \"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n                \"sessionTimeout\":     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n                \"maxSessionDuration\": &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n                \"podTemplate\": map[string]interface{}{\n                    \"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n                        \"containers\": []interface{}{\n                            map[string]interface{}{\n                                \"name\":  \"agent\",\n                                \"image\": \"python:3.11-slim\",\n                            },\n                        },\n                    },\n                },\n                \"ports\": []interface{}{\n                    map[string]interface{}{\n                        \"port\":     int64(8080),\n                        \"protocol\": \"HTTP\",\n                    },\n                },\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n\nfunc CreateTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace string) *unstructured.Unstructured {\n    return &unstructured.Unstructured{\n        Object: map[string]interface{}{\n            \"apiVersion\": \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\",\n            \"kind\":       \"CodeInterpreter\",\n            \"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n                \"name\":      name,\n                \"namespace\": namespace,\n            },\n            \"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n                \"template\": map[string]interface{}{\n                    \"image\": \"python:3.11-slim\",\n                },\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n\nfunc CreateTestSandbox(name, namespace, sessionID string) *unstructured.Unstructured {\n    return &unstructured.Unstructured{\n        Object: map[string]interface{}{\n            \"apiVersion\": \"agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\",\n            \"kind\":       \"Sandbox\",\n            \"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n                \"name\":      name,\n                \"namespace\": namespace,\n                \"labels\": map[string]interface{}{\n                    \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\": sessionID,\n                },\n            },\n            \"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n                \"replicas\": int64(1),\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n\nfunc CreateTestSandboxInfo(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n    return &types.SandboxInfo{\n        SessionID:    sessionID,\n        SandboxID:    \"sandbox-\" + sessionID,\n        SandboxName:  \"test-sandbox\",\n        WorkloadName: \"test-workload\",\n        Namespace:    \"default\",\n        Kind:         \"AgentRuntime\",\n        Status:       \"running\",\n        CreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n        ExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n        PodIP:        \"10.244.1.5\",\n        EntryPoints: []types.SandboxEntryPoint{\n            {\n                Protocol: \"HTTP\",\n                Endpoint: \"10.244.1.5:8080\",\n                Path:     \"/\",\n            },\n        },\n        LastActivityAt: time.Now(),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Component-Specific Testing\n\n### 1. API Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/api/`)\n\n#### Test Coverage\n\n**`response_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ Error response formatting\n- ‚úÖ JSON response formatting\n- ‚úÖ Error code formatting\n\n**Future tests needed:**\n- `types_test.go`: Type validation and serialization\n\n#### Example Test Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validation(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        req     api.CreateSandboxRequest\n        wantErr bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"valid request\",\n            req: api.CreateSandboxRequest{\n                Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n                Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n                Namespace: \"default\",\n            },\n            wantErr: false,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"missing kind\",\n            req: api.CreateSandboxRequest{\n                Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n                Namespace: \"default\",\n            },\n            wantErr: true,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"invalid kind\",\n            req: api.CreateSandboxRequest{\n                Kind:      \"InvalidKind\",\n                Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n                Namespace: \"default\",\n            },\n            wantErr: true,\n        },\n    }\n\n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            err := tt.req.Validate()\n            if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n                t.Errorf(\"CreateSandboxRequest.Validate() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n            }\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Controller Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/controller/`)\n\n#### Test Coverage\n\n**`sandbox_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ Create AgentRuntime sandbox\n- ‚úÖ Create CodeInterpreter sandbox\n- ‚úÖ Get session\n- ‚úÖ Delete session\n- ‚úÖ Build sandbox CRs\n- ‚úÖ Build entry points\n- ‚úÖ Generate sandbox names\n- ‚úÖ Error handling scenarios\n\n#### Test Patterns\n\n```go\nfunc TestSandboxController_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n    fixtures := NewTestFixtures(t)\n    defer fixtures.Cleanup()\n\n    t.Run(\"successfully creates sandbox\", func(t *testing.T) {\n        ctx := context.Background()\n        controller := NewSandboxController(fixtures.MockK8s, fixtures.Store)\n\n        req := &api.CreateSandboxRequest{\n            Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n        }\n\n        agentRuntime := CreateTestAgentRuntime(\"test-runtime\", \"default\")\n        sandboxCR := CreateTestSandbox(\"test-runtime-abc123\", \"default\", \"session-123\")\n\n        fixtures.MockK8s.On(\"GetAgentRuntime\", mock.Anything, \"default\", \"test-runtime\").Return(agentRuntime, nil)\n        fixtures.MockK8s.On(\"CreateSandbox\", ctx, \"default\", mock.AnythingOfType(\"*unstructured.Unstructured\")).Return(sandboxCR, nil)\n        fixtures.MockK8s.On(\"GetPodIP\", mock.Anything, mock.Anything, \"default\", mock.Anything).Return(\"10.244.1.5\", nil)\n\n        resp, err := controller.CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(ctx, req)\n\n        require.NoError(t, err)\n        require.NotNil(t, resp)\n        assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SessionID)\n        assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SandboxID)\n        assert.Equal(t, \"HTTP\", resp.EntryPoints[0].Protocol)\n\n        fixtures.MockK8s.AssertExpectations(t)\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Handler Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/`)\n\n#### Test Coverage\n\n**`handler_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ Create AgentRuntime sandbox handler\n- ‚úÖ Create CodeInterpreter sandbox handler\n- ‚úÖ Get session handler\n- ‚úÖ Delete session handler\n- ‚úÖ Health check handler\n- ‚úÖ Request body validation\n- ‚úÖ Error responses\n\n**`sandbox_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ Handle delete sandbox\n- ‚úÖ Handle SandboxClaim deletion\n- ‚úÖ Error handling\n\n#### Test Patterns\n\n```go\nfunc TestHandler_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n    gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n    mockCtrl := new(MockSandboxController)\n    router := setupRouter(mockCtrl)\n\n    t.Run(\"successfully creates sandbox\", func(t *testing.T) {\n        expectedResp := &api.CreateSandboxResponse{\n            SessionID:   \"session-123\",\n            SandboxID:   \"sandbox-123\",\n            SandboxName: \"test-runtime-abc123\",\n            EntryPoints: []api.EntryPoint{\n                {\n                    Protocol: \"HTTP\",\n                    Endpoint: \"10.244.1.5:8080\",\n                    Port:     8080,\n                },\n            },\n            CreatedAt: time.Now().Format(time.RFC3339),\n            ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour).Format(time.RFC3339),\n        }\n\n        mockCtrl.On(\"CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox\", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(expectedResp, nil)\n\n        reqBody := map[string]interface{}{\n            \"kind\":      \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"name\":      \"test-runtime\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\",\n        }\n        body, _ := json.Marshal(reqBody)\n\n        req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/v1/agent-runtime\", bytes.NewBuffer(body))\n        req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n        w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n\n        router.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n\n        assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n\n        var resp api.CreateSandboxResponse\n        err := json.Unmarshal(w.Body.Bytes(), &resp)\n        require.NoError(t, err)\n        assert.Equal(t, \"session-123\", resp.SessionID)\n\n        mockCtrl.AssertExpectations(t)\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Client Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/client/`)\n\n#### Test Coverage\n\n**`k8s_client_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ Get AgentRuntime\n- ‚úÖ Get CodeInterpreter\n- ‚úÖ Create sandbox\n- ‚úÖ Get sandbox\n- ‚úÖ Delete sandbox\n- ‚úÖ Error handling (not found scenarios)\n\n#### Test Patterns\n\n```go\nfunc TestK8sClient_GetAgentRuntime(t *testing.T) {\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    err := v1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    agentRuntime := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n        },\n        Spec: v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n            MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n        },\n    }\n\n    agentRuntimeUnstructured, err := runtime.DefaultUnstructuredConverter.ToUnstructured(agentRuntime)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    agentRuntimeObj := &unstructured.Unstructured{Object: agentRuntimeUnstructured}\n    agentRuntimeObj.SetAPIVersion(\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\")\n    agentRuntimeObj.SetKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n\n    dynamicClient := fake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n    gvr := schema.GroupVersionResource{\n        Group:    \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\",\n        Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n        Resource: \"agentruntimes\",\n    }\n\n    _, err = dynamicClient.Resource(gvr).Namespace(\"default\").Create(context.Background(), agentRuntimeObj, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    k8sClient := &wmClient.K8sClient{\n        dynamic:  dynamicClient,\n        gvrAgent: gvr,\n    }\n\n    t.Run(\"successfully gets agent runtime\", func(t *testing.T) {\n        result, err := k8sClient.GetAgentRuntime(context.Background(), \"default\", \"test-runtime\")\n\n        require.NoError(t, err)\n        require.NotNil(t, result)\n        assert.Equal(t, \"test-runtime\", result.GetName())\n    })\n\n    t.Run(\"agent runtime not found\", func(t *testing.T) {\n        _, err := k8sClient.GetAgentRuntime(context.Background(), \"default\", \"nonexistent\")\n\n        require.Error(t, err)\n        assert.True(t, apierrors.IsNotFound(err))\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### 5. GC Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/gc/`)\n\n#### Test Coverage\n\n**`collector_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ NewGCCollector initialization\n- ‚úÖ Collect with no candidates\n- ‚úÖ Collect expired sandbox\n- ‚úÖ Collect idle sandbox\n- ‚úÖ Dry run mode\n- ‚úÖ Session not found handling\n- ‚úÖ SandboxClaim deletion\n\n**`policy_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ DefaultGCConfig\n- ‚úÖ NewGCPolicy initialization\n- ‚úÖ Label selector validation\n- ‚úÖ Namespace filtering\n- ‚úÖ Expiration detection\n- ‚úÖ Idle detection\n- ‚úÖ Orphan detection\n- ‚úÖ ShouldGC logic\n\n**`scheduler_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ NewGCScheduler initialization\n- ‚úÖ RunOnce execution\n- ‚úÖ Start/Stop lifecycle\n- ‚úÖ Config updates\n- ‚úÖ Error handling\n\n**`metrics_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n- ‚úÖ Metrics initialization\n- ‚úÖ Record operations\n- ‚úÖ Concurrent access\n\n#### Test Patterns\n\n```go\nfunc TestGCCollector_Collect_ExpiredSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n    mockStore := &mockStore{}\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n\n    scheme.AddKnownTypes(schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"},\n        &unstructured.Unstructured{},\n        &unstructured.UnstructuredList{},\n    )\n\n    fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleDynamicClientWithCustomListKinds(scheme, map[schema.GroupVersionResource]string{\n        SandboxGVR:       \"SandboxList\",\n        SandboxClaimGVR:  \"SandboxClaimList\",\n    })\n\n    sessionID := \"test-session\"\n    sandboxInfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n        SessionID:        sessionID,\n        SandboxID:        \"test-sandbox\",\n        SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n        Kind:             \"Sandbox\",\n        LastActivityAt:   time.Now(),\n        ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(1 * time.Hour),\n    }\n\n    mockStore.On(\"GetSandbox\", mock.Anything, sessionID).Return(sandboxInfo, nil)\n    mockStore.On(\"DeleteSandboxBySessionID\", mock.Anything, sessionID).Return(nil)\n\n    sandbox := buildTestSandbox(\"test-sandbox\", \"default\", sessionID, 24*time.Hour)\n    fakeClient.Resource(SandboxGVR).Namespace(\"default\").Create(context.Background(), sandbox, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n\n    config := &GCConfig{\n        MaxAge:        1 * time.Hour,\n        IdleTimeout:   15 * time.Minute,\n        DryRun:        false,\n        Namespaces:    []string{},\n        LabelSelector: \"\",\n    }\n    policy, _ := NewGCPolicy(config)\n    metrics := NewGCMetrics()\n\n    collector := NewGCCollector(fakeClient, mockStore, config, policy, metrics)\n\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    result, err := collector.Collect(ctx)\n\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.NotNil(t, result)\n    assert.Equal(t, 1, result.Scanned)\n    assert.Equal(t, 1, result.Candidates)\n    assert.Equal(t, 1, result.Deleted)\n    assert.Equal(t, 0, result.Errors)\n\n    mockStore.AssertExpectations(t)\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Config Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/config/`)\n\n#### Test Coverage\n\n**`c