pkg/apis/runtime/**'\n\njobs:\n  test:\n    name: Unit Tests\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout code\n        uses: actions/checkout@v3\n\n      - name: Set up Go\n        uses: actions/setup-go@v4\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24'\n\n      - name: Download dependencies\n        run: go mod download\n\n      - name: Run tests\n        run: |\n          go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... \\\n            -v \\\n            -race \\\n            -coverprofile=coverage.out \\\n            -covermode=atomic\n\n      - name: Generate coverage report\n        run: go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n\n      - name: Upload coverage\n        uses: codecov/codecov-action@v3\n        with:\n          files: ./coverage.out\n          flags: workloadmanager\n\n  lint:\n    name: Lint\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout code\n        uses: actions/checkout@v3\n\n      - name: Set up Go\n        uses: actions/setup-go@v4\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24'\n\n      - name: Run golangci-lint\n        uses: golangci/golangci-lint-action@v3\n        with:\n          version: latest\n          working-directory: pkg/workloadmanager\n```\n\n### Pre-commit Hooks\n\n```yaml\n# .pre-commit-config.yaml\nrepos:\n  - repo: local\n    hooks:\n      - id: go-test-workloadmanager\n        name: Go test workloadmanager\n        entry: bash -c 'cd pkg/workloadmanager && go test ./... -short'\n        language: system\n        pass_filenames: false\n\n      - id: go-lint-workloadmanager\n        name: Go lint workloadmanager\n        entry: bash -c 'golangci-lint run pkg/workloadmanager/...'\n        language: system\n        pass_filenames: false\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### Test Naming Conventions\n\n```go\n// Function being tested\nfunc Test<Component>_<Function>(t *testing.T)\n\n// Specific scenario\nfunc Test<Component>_<Function>_<Scenario>(t *testing.T)\n\n// Example\nfunc TestSandboxController_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSandboxController_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_NotFound(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n### Table-Driven Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestFunction(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        input   InputType\n        want    OutputType\n        wantErr bool\n        errType error\n    }{\n        {\n            name:    \"valid input\",\n            input:   validInput,\n            want:    expectedOutput,\n            wantErr: false,\n        },\n        {\n            name:    \"invalid input\",\n            input:   invalidInput,\n            want:    nil,\n            wantErr: true,\n            errType: ErrInvalidInput,\n        },\n    }\n\n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            got, err := Function(tt.input)\n\n            if tt.wantErr {\n                require.Error(t, err)\n                if tt.errType != nil {\n                    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, tt.errType)\n                }\n                return\n            }\n\n            require.NoError(t, err)\n            assert.Equal(t, tt.want, got)\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Test Cleanup\n\n```go\nfunc TestFunction(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup\n    fixtures := NewTestFixtures(t)\n    defer fixtures.Cleanup()\n\n    // Test code\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n### Assertions\n\n```go\n// Use require for fatal assertions (test continues)\nrequire.NoError(t, err)\nrequire.NotNil(t, result)\n\n// Use assert for non-fatal assertions (test continues)\nassert.Equal(t, expected, actual)\nassert.Contains(t, str, substring)\nassert.True(t, condition)\n```\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Test Isolation\n\n- Each test should be independent\n- Use table-driven tests for similar scenarios\n- Clean up resources in defer statements\n\n### Concurrent Testing\n\n```go\nfunc TestConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T) {\n    var wg sync.WaitGroup\n    for i := 0; i < 100; i++ {\n        wg.Add(1)\n        go func() {\n            defer wg.Done()\n            // Test code\n        }()\n    }\n    wg.Wait()\n}\n```\n\n### Benchmark Tests (Optional)\n\n```go\nfunc BenchmarkFunction(b *testing.B) {\n    for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n        Function(testInput)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\n### Test Documentation\n\nEach test file should include:\n1. Purpose of the tests\n2. Test data sources\n3. Mock behavior documentation\n\n```go\n// TestSandboxController provides unit tests for the SandboxController.\n//\n// The tests cover:\n// - Sandbox creation for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n// - Session retrieval and deletion\n// - Error handling and edge cases\n//\n// Mock objects are used to isolate the controller from external dependencies\n// such as Kubernetes API and Redis storage.\npackage controller_test\n```\n\n### Comments in Tests\n\n```go\nt.Run(\"successfully creates sandbox\", func(t *testing.T) {\n    // Arrange\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    controller := NewSandboxController(fixtures.MockK8s, fixtures.Store)\n    req := &api.CreateSandboxRequest{Name: \"test-runtime\", Namespace: \"default\"}\n\n    // Act\n    resp, err := controller.CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(ctx, req)\n\n    // Assert\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    require.NotNil(t, resp)\n    assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SessionID)\n})\n```\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n### Potential Areas for Additional Testing\n\n1. **Integration Tests**: Full-stack tests with real Kubernetes cluster (kind/minikube)\n2. **End-to-End Tests**: Tests covering complete user workflows\n3. **Load Tests**: Performance tests under high load\n4. **Fuzz Testing**: Property-based testing for input validation\n5. **Contract Tests**: API contract verification\n\n### Test Infrastructure Improvements\n\n1. **Test Container Management**: Better setup/teardown for external dependencies\n2. **Golden File Testing**: For complex output validation\n3. **Test Data Generation**: Programmatic test data creation\n4. **Coverage Visualiza